text: The Supreme Council (, Joğorku Keñeş, جوعورقۇ كەڭەش; , Verkhovnyy Sovet) is the unicameral Parliament of the Kyrgyz Republic. It was known as the Supreme Soviet of the Kirghiz Soviet Socialist Republic until 1991. The parliament has 120 seats with members elected for a five-year term by party-list proportional voting. ==Other websites== *Parliament website *Kyrgyzstan information page on the website of Asian Medical Institute Kyrgyzstan Category:Politics of Kyrgyzstan Category:1990s establishments in Kyrgyzstan Category:Organizations based in Kyrgyzstan Category:Unicameral legislatures
